cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper proposes a novel approach for random access in machine-type communications (MTC) in cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves coding techniques and analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The proposed approach involves changes in the medium access control layer, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the support of MTC users, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses security aspects of the proposed approach, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
